# ============================================================
# Supabase Cloud Login & Save Configuration
# ============================================================
# STEP-BY-STEP SETUP:
#
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com and create a free project
#
# 2. Enable OAuth providers:
#    → Go to Authentication → Providers
#    → Enable "Google" and enter your Google OAuth Client ID/Secret
#      (get from https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials)
#    → Enable "Discord" and enter your Discord Client ID/Secret
#      (get from https://discord.com/developers/applications)
#    → Set Redirect URL in both providers to:
#      https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
#
# 3. Copy these two values from your Supabase project:
#    → Go to Settings → API
#    → Copy "Project URL" → paste as VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#    → Copy "anon public" key → paste as VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#
# 4. Run the SQL from supabase_schema.sql in your Supabase SQL Editor
#
# 5. Rename this file to .env (remove the .example part)
#
# 6. Restart the dev server: npm run dev
# ============================================================

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here
